IRS990.MissionDesc: SUPPORT CANCER AND OTHER MEDICAL RESEARCH, CONTRIBUTING TO LOCAL MEDICAL CHARITABLE EFFORTS AND PROVIDING SCHOLARSHIPS AND GRANTS TO DESERVING LOCAL STUDENTS PURSUING A CAREER IN A MEDICALLY-RELATED FIELD.
IRS990.Desc: GRANTS AND FELLOWSHIPS TO MAJOR UNIVERSITITES MEDICAL RESEARCH PROGRAMS. SCHOLARSHIPS AND GRANTS AWARDEED TO LOCAL WINFIELD STUDENTS PURSUING A CAREER IN A HEALTHCARE RELATED FIELD AT A VARIETY OF UNIVERSITIES AND COMMUNITY COLLEGES. ADDITIONALLY, FUNDS ARE AWARDED FOR NEEDED MEDICAL EQUIPMENT TO INSTITUTIONS THAT QUALIFY.

IRS990ScheduleA.FactsAndCircumstancesTestTxt: 1) PUBLIC SUPPORT WAS 24.02% IN 2022, ABOVE THE 10% BENCHMARK. 2) BOARD MEMBERS REPRESENT BROAD PUBLIC SUPPORT. THEY HAVE SIXTY-TWO BOARD MEMBERS AS OF JUNE 30, 2023. 3) GRANTS AND FELLOWSHIPS TO MEDICAL RESEARCH ARE AWARDED. THE RESEARCH OUTCOMES, WOULD BENEFIT THE GENERAL PUBLIC. ADDITIONALLY, THE HL SNYDER MEDICAL FOUNDATION AWARDS SCHOLARSHIPS TO STUDENTS PURSUING AN EDUCATION IN THE MEDICAL FIELD. APPLICATIONS FOR SCHOLARSHIPS ARE ACCEPTED FROM THE PUBLIC, AND THE GENERAL PUBLIC HAS THE OPPORTUNITY TO APPLY FOR THE SCHOLARSHIPS. 4) THE HL SNYDER MEDICAL FOUNDATION 20,583 TO LOCAL SCHOOL DISTRICT FOR HEARING TESTING MACHINES, SEVEN AUTOMATED DEFIBULATORS AND BOOKS FOR THE HEALTH CARE COURSE OF STUDY. THE FOUNDATION GAVE 36,479 TO THE CITY FOR EMS FOR LIFE PACK W/ ALS CAPABILITES. THE FOUNDATION GAVE 12,810 TO A NONPROFIT FOR SEVEN AED MACHINES AND TRAINING ON THE EQUIPMENT. THE FOUNDATION GAVE 56,168 TO A LOCAL HEALTHCARE FOUNDATION FOR A STATUS URINALYSIS MACHINE, SIMULATOR, RECUMBRENT BICYLE AND 50,000 WHICH WAS ACCURED AS A GRANT PAYABLE AND A SURGICAL WING REMODEL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE I, PAGE 1, PART I, LINE 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: UPDATES ON THE RESEARCH PERFORMED BY THE ORGANIZATIONS AWARDED RESEARCH GRANTS ARE REPORTED BACK TO THE H.L. SNYDER MEDICAL FOUNDATION ANNUALLY. THE RESEARCH COMMITTEE, COMPRISED OF TRUSTEES REVIEWS THE REPORT, AND MAKE RECCOMENDATIONS TO THE FULL BOARD. WITH EACH RESEARCH GRANT THERE IS AN AGREEMENT INDICATING PARAMETERS OF WHAT THE RESEARCH GRANT FUNDS MAY BE USED FOR. SCHOLARSHIPS FOR STUDENTS ARE PAID DIRECTLY TO THE EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTIONS FOR TUITION. STUDENTS DO NOT RECEIVE THE FUNDS DIRECTLY. WITH SCHOLARSHIPS THERE IS A MINIMUM GRADE AVERAGE REQUIRED OF 3.0, AND THE STUDENT MUST BE ATTENDING AN ACCREDITED COLLEGE, AND BE A JUNIOR IN COLLEGE WORKING TOWARD A DEGREE IN THE MEDICAL AREA OF STUDY. GRANTS AWARDED FOR STUDENTS REQUIRE THAT THE STUDENT MUST BE AT LEAST A FULL TIME STUDENT.
